  "texts": [
    "However, stemming can often confound superficially similar yet unrelated words (e.g.",
    "universal, university, universe would all be stemmed to univers).",
    "Lemmatization considers a language's full vocabulary, as well as the surrounding context of a word and their POS to collapse a word down to its canonical form, or lemma.",
    "For example, \"infectious\" again becomes \"infect\" but \"better\" becomes \"good\", a relationship not captured by simple stemming.",
    "Once stemmed or lemmatized, stop word removal can also be considered (see Paradigm 1)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}